snippet: In a bipartisan vote, the Senate Banking Committee approved the bill 13 to 9, but it is unlikely to come to a floor vote anytime soon because not enough Democrats support it.
abstract: Senate Banking Committee approves legislation to wind down Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac and reshape the mortgage finance system; sparse support among Democrats means measure is unlikely to become law.
lead_paragraph: In a bipartisan vote, the Senate Banking Committee approved the bill 13 to 9, but it is unlikely to come to a floor vote anytime soon because not enough Democrats support it.
